  "prompt": "How is the M27 IAR issued at the US Marines squad level? One for each fire-team, or mixed with the M249 SAW?",
  "response": "The M27 Infantry Automatic Rifle (IAR) is issued at the US Marines squad level to replace the M249 Squad Automatic Weapon (SAW) in each fire-team. Specifically, each Marine rifle squad typically consists of three fire-teams, and each fire-team is equipped with one M27 IAR. This means each squad has three M27 IARs, with one assigned to the automatic rifleman in each fire-team.\n\nThe transition from the M249 SAW to the M27 IAR was part of an effort to enhance the squad's firepower and maneuverability. The M27 offers greater accuracy and reliability compared to the M249, while still providing the necessary rate of fire for suppressive purposes. Thus, the M27 IAR fully replaced the M249 SAW within each fire-team, rather than being mixed with it.",
